<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-22T06:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-22T06:44:00-05:00" n="521" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/568: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-22T11:00:00-00:44">May 22,
                                    1942—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 1:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>159. Referring to my 158, May 21. On reconsideration Secretary Simpson,
                            by President’s instructions, notified Wehrle last evening of invitation
                            for all Germans to leave Liberia. It is understood five will leave
                            tomorrow by plane and all others are given 2 weeks within which to
                            depart. Any further developments will be telegraphed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>